    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@kky The fact that the default theme as very few rules is normal and on purpose. I know it looks counterintuitive but this was done to avoid any styling collision with the host website using instantsearch.js.\n\nSo we deliberately choosed to have a very RAW theme and let useres do their own theming by overriding classes.\n\nThat's why we still have all the css classes defined but empty in the unminified version: http://cdn.jsdelivr.net/instantsearch.js/1/instantsearch.css\n\nI will try to explain this in clear words in the documentation and fix this 404.\n\nThanks a lot for the feedback.\n",
